  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't know whether it was while the boat was in the harbor or just as we were leaving.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "I think it was while-- while the boat was still in the harbor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And this man, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I think his wife and two girls were already in Cuba.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "Anyway, they-- the Cubans fished them out of the water, and they took him to a hospital.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And when he had recuperated, they shipped him out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "They wouldn't let him stay.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Anyway, during all this time, the JDC, the Jewish Distribution Committee, I guess that is, sent somebody over to Cuba to try to-- to talk to the government and to try to get them to let us stay in the Havana.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "Apparently they offered some money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "They assured the Cubans that we wouldn't be a drag on the economy, that we would not be working there, number one.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "We wouldn't be allowed to work and that they would-- they would supply money for our upkeep, for rent, until we could get into the United States.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "Now, remember, I told you, most of these passengers on the ship also had these numbers, which eventually would allow you to get a visa to the United States.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "By the way, there were-- there were, I think, around 30 people who were not Jewish and who were on this cruise [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think for other reasons.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And they actually got off in Cuba.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember but, of course, that one time that we were actually talking to our relatives, they gave us some information, although they tried to be very optimistic.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I've read subsequently that there was a committee of passengers who-- and they met regularly with the Captain.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
